            <h1 class="display-3">Eligibility</h1>
            <hr>
            <div class="list container text-justify">
                <p>The sections of the society as enlisted under Section 12 of the Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 entitled for free legal services are:</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>A member of a Scheduled Caste or Scheduled Tribe</li>
                    <li>A victim of trafficking in human beings or beggar as referred to in Article 23 of the
                        Constitution of India.</li>
                    <li>A woman or a child</li>
                    <li>A mentally ill or otherwise disabled person</li>
                    <li>A person under circumstances of undeserved want such as being a victim of a mass
                        disaster, ethnic violence, caste atrocity, flood, drought, earthquake or industrial disaster
                    </li>
                    <li>An industrial workman/workwoman</li>
                    <li>Person in custody</li>
                    <li>a person in receipt of annual income less than 3 lakh per annum, if the case is before a
                        Court other than the Supreme Court, and less than Rs 5 Lakh, if the case is before the
                        Supreme Court.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            <h1 class="display-3">Know Your Rights</h1>
            <hr>
            <div class="list container text-justify">
                <p>Here are some of the rights a civilian should be aware of:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>If a Police Officer refuses to lodge First Information Report then they could be prisoned
                        for 6 months to 1 year.</li>
                    <li>If their gas cylinder blasts during the cooking of food then the gas agency is liable to
                        pay Rs. 50 lakh to the victim as compensation. To claim this compensation consumers
                        need to lodge an FIR to the nearest police station and submit it to the concerned gas
                        agency.</li>
                    <li>No any woman can be arrested after 6:00 pm to 6:00 am. In case of only dire necessity,
                        only a female police can in special circumstances arrest a female between 6 pm to 6 am
                        and can be detained only in a Police Station which is an All Women one.</li>
                    <li>One can approach to any high (including 5 & 7 star) or low star rated hotel for drinking
                        water and to use their loo/washroom.</li>
                    <li>At the time of driving if the 100ml. blood contains more than 30mg. of alcohol then the
                        police can arrest anyone without a warrant.</li>
                    <li>Snatching the key from any two-wheeler or four-wheeler vehicle by the traffic
                        personnel is illegal. One can launch legal proceedings against these types of
                        misbehaviour.</li>
                    <li>Every person must be told the grounds for the arrest at the time.</li>
                    <li>The police must inform and allow the accused to immediately inform family or friends
                        about the arrest and the place of detention. And allow the accused to consult a lawyer
                        immediately.</li>
                    <li>To adopt a child there should be an age gap of 21 years between the adopter and the
                        child.</li>
                    <li>It is legal for unmarried couples to stay-in hotels with true identification but the age of
                        couple should be more than 18 years.</li>
                    <li>If any organisation is not giving salary to its employees, then the employees vested with
                        the right to file the FIR against the organisation within the next 3 years. </li>
                    <li>MRP stands for Maximum Retail Price and the shopkeeper cannot trade anything
                        beyond the mentioned price on any manufactured goods. Also the customers are vested
                        with the right to bargain for less than the printed price of a commodity.</li>
                    <li>One cannot fined twice a day for the same reason. </li>
                    <li>Male constable doesn’t have the right to arrest women. Only after the written order
                        from the magistrate, a male policeman can arrest a woman. </li>
                    <li>No company can fire a pregnant woman. It may be punishable by a maximum of 3 years
                        of imprisonment.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
